 belong.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I have a question, why lock them instead of just moving them?<br>
<br>
Moving them may result in &quot;where's my post?&quot;<br>
<br>
Locking them may result in &quot;You locked my post!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> &quot;<br>
<br>
Locking them and moving them would result in both.<br>
<br>
Unless it's a repost and you can redirect the poster or mention that a good scan of the board would find plenty of posts on the same topic, or unless it's a troll/flame/etc, I am curious why you need to lock them at all?<br>
<br>
<br>
As an aside...<br>
<br>
I think it would be neat to see what would happen if we just shut down &quot;General&quot; for a week or two.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll also note that finding something in sub-forums is easier, so long as the sub-forums consistantly have the right topical information.  &quot;Divide and conquer&quot; search methods require accuracy to actually save you time.  Searching through 5 pages of &quot;pets,&quot; 5 pages of &quot;spells,&quot; and finally 5 pages of &quot;Class balance,&quot; to finally find the post you are looking for is worse than simply doing a linear search through 15 pages of general. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tangting01>TangTing01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#333333>(12/29/02 2:37:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8279.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Excess Forumage?</span><hr size=1> I think they get locked when they are talking about well covered territory.  I think it's the mods way of saying, &quot;Go to the forum and do a search&quot;.  I will say that having a search function that covered all forums would make that much easier.<br>
